Three weeks since Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan unveiled the Eskom special paper, it’s set to be discussed by Parliament’s Public Enterprises Committee. The plan contains the roadmap for unbundling the power utility including the establishment of a transmission company that should be set up by March. PARLIAMENT - Public Enterprises committee will debate the Eskom special paper on Wednesday. Last month, Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan unveiled the special paper. Gordhan says there is plans to break the power utility up into three separate entities namely Transmission, Generation and Distribution. READ: Gordhan outlines Eskom's future plans He says splitting the utility into three separate entities may offer solutions. Parliament also approved a R59-billion bailout over the next two years. This comes on the back of Eskom announcing a new CEO for the company.